snippet.textDisplay: I was bullied relentlessly in middle school, and my VP never believed me, she thought I was always playing victim. One particularly bad morning, I was being harassed and hit and slammed into the lockers. There were about 3-4 girls ganging up on me. I was able to escape, but I told someone what happened and was sent the principle's office. I had to deal with the same VP and she again didn't believe me, EVEN THOUGH MY ATTACK WAS ON TAPE! I was suspended  for the rest of the day for being attacked in the hallways, and the attackers were never punished. This was my second suspension that year. The first was also due to the VP not believing me.

Been all down hill from there, that was literally the last year i liked school.

snippet.textDisplay:
The school system can never handle bullies if they won't enact rules and punishments that properly punish the bullies. The reason they won't do this is because they fear the parents of the bully and the victim equally. It should not be this way, it should and probably is illegal to handle things this way. But the school pretends they're the judge and jury in this cases until you take them to court and show them who the real boss is. If your kid is a little shit who picks on others the law needs to be laid down and the angry parent needs to be told to go fuck themself. End of story.


My high school was playing cover up for all the upper classes. Every year on the first Friday of the year there was this thing they named "Freshmen Friday" where all the upper classes chased down and wedgied the freshmen after school was out. We had all heard rumors about this but the teachers and student council who knew it was happening, ensured us that it was not a thing that actually happened. The most terrifying thing about this? Having a Senior who is old enough to drive cut off your escape by pulling infront of you in the road and leaping out of their car to attack you. The only reason any of this came to light and the school was forced to address it was because one of my friends fled into a busy street to escape then got smashed in the face by the side mirror of a passing car. What these assholes had convinced themselves was light hearted hazing had now turned into a 14 year old stumbling into a grocery store with blood pouring down his face. I am not remotely saddened that school doesn't exist anymore.
